.TH CONFLUEX 1 "May 2026" "confluex 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
confluex \- export Confluence pages to Markdown
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B confluex setup
.br
.B confluex plan --page-id
.I id
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B confluex export --page-id
.I id
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B confluex
is a token-authenticated command line tool for planning and exporting
Confluence page scopes to Markdown.
.PP
.B setup
saves reusable user configuration.
.B plan
checks the selected page scope and writes reports without downloading page
payloads or attachments.
.B export
writes Markdown pages, attachments, and reports.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
Interactively save the Confluence base URL and token in the user configuration
file. The token prompt does not echo input.
.TP
.B plan
Build the selected page scope, validate page access, and write reports without
materializing Markdown payloads or attachment files.
.TP
.B export
Build the selected page scope, write Markdown payloads, retain downloaded
attachments, and write reports.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Required selection
.TP
.BI --page-id " id"
Root Confluence page id for
.B plan
or
.BR export .
.SS Output control
.TP
.BI --out " path"
Output directory. If omitted, Confluex generates an output directory.
.TP
.B --zip
For
.BR export ,
create a ZIP archive beside the Markdown output root.
.TP
.B --resume
For
.BR export ,
reuse a compatible incomplete output root selected by
.BR --out .
.SS Scope control
.TP
.B --include-children
Include the recursive Confluence child tree of the root page in the selected
scope. If omitted, Confluex does not traverse child pages.
.TP
.BI --link-depth " n"
Follow supported internal links up to
.I n
hops from pages already in scope.
.TP
.BI --max-find-candidates " n"
Inspect at most
.I n
title-resolution candidates per link.
.SS Safety limits
.TP
.BI --max-pages " n"
Stop after
.I n
processed pages.
.TP
.BI --max-download-mib " n"
Stop after downloading
.I n
MiB in total.
.SS Runtime behavior
.TP
.B --no-fail-fast
Continue after page-local runtime failures.
.TP
.B --keep-metadata
Persist page metadata files such as
.I _info.txt
and
.IR _storage.xml .
.TP
.BI --sleep-ms " n"
Sleep
.I n
milliseconds between processed pages.
.SS Logging and configuration
.TP
.BI --env-file " file"
Load public configuration from an explicit env file.
.TP
.BI --log-file " file"
Write a persistent log artifact.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration precedence is command-line options, explicit env file, default
current-directory
.IR .confluex.env ,
user config written by
.BR setup ,
process environment, then no value.
.PP
Supported public configuration names include
.BR CONFLUEX_CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL ,
.BR CONFLUEX_CONFLUENCE_TOKEN ,
.BR CONFLUEX_OUTPUT_ROOT ,
.BR CONFLUEX_LOG_FILE ,
.BR CONFLUEX_MAX_PAGES ,
.BR CONFLUEX_MAX_DOWNLOAD_MIB ,
.BR CONFLUEX_SLEEP_MS ,
.BR CONFLUEX_MAX_FIND_CANDIDATES ,
and
.BR CONFLUEX_LINK_DEPTH .
.PP
Tokens are used as Bearer token values for Confluence requests. Confluex does
not print token values in setup prompts, command output, logs, or reports.
.SH OUTPUTS
.TP
.I summary.txt
Run outcome summary.
.TP
.I manifest.tsv
Selected page inventory.
.TP
.I resolved-links.tsv
Supported links resolved into the selected scope.
.TP
.I unresolved-links.tsv
Supported links that could not be resolved into the selected scope.
.TP
.I failed-pages.tsv
Page-local failures.
.TP
.I scope-findings.tsv
Scope and discovery findings.
.PP
.B export
also writes Markdown page payloads and retained attachments under the output
root. With
.BR --zip ,
it creates a ZIP archive beside the output root.
.SH REPORTS
Reports are tab-separated or line-oriented text files intended for operator
review and automation. A successful
.B plan
or
.B export
run writes the report set under the selected output root.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success, success with findings, or help.
.TP
.B 1
Rejected invocation or setup validation failure.
.TP
.B 3
Configured stop condition.
.TP
.B 4
Runtime failure.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by signal.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/confluex/config.json
User config on Linux and XDG environments when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is set.
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/confluex/config.json
User config on Linux and XDG environments when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is not set.
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\econfluex\econfig.json
User config on Windows.
.TP
.I ./.confluex.env
Default current-directory env file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Configure reusable access:
.B confluex setup
.TP
Validate access and inspect the planned scope:
.B confluex plan --page-id 12345 --out ./plan
.TP
Export Markdown and create a ZIP archive:
.B confluex export --page-id 12345 --out ./dump --zip
.TP
Resume an incomplete export:
.B confluex export --page-id 12345 --out ./dump --resume
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR npm (1)
